        ],
        [
          "Cicatriz - Bishop of Tijuana",
          "You have heard that Cicatriz also uses the spirits of the dead to aid his quest for knowledge.  Given his interests, he could be a valuable ally for your pack."
        ],
        [
          "Valentin/Valentina Ulyanenko",
          "Your pack's ductus, and a bit of a fanatic when it comes to their hatred of elders and outrage at any sire's mistreatment of a childe.  You appreciate their fervor, especially the role they played in getting you out from under your own sire's thumb."
        ],
        [
          "Aleksandru/Aleksandra Balcescu",
          "You can symapthize with them. Their sire was of that Inconnu's line, and she lived up to the reputation of tyrannical Tzimisce elders. Balcescu s a bit standoff-ish, you think. Old habits die hard, and there is still a good deal of the Old World castle-dwelling Tzimisce Carpathian in him. But those very traits of hospitality and courtliness make him a fine abbot to your pack."
        ],
        [
          "Cameron Spelman",
          "Fostered to the Ventrue Primogen of Worcester MA, you met them when your pack infiltrated the city to examine some archival records held at the Higgins Armory Museum. The latest addition to your pack."
        ],
        [
          "Starting Goals",
          "These are recomendations, not mandates."
        ],
        [
          "the questions around your monomancy are a deep secret.  It might be best if the Inquisition's influence in San Diego were lessened.   Try to work for the candidiate who is most skeptical of giving them free rein."
        ],
        [
          "Make contact wtih Cicatriz and see if you can ally to utilize your talents to seek out those elders you've heard of."
        ],
        [
          "The Tremere chantry could be a valuable resource.  Seek out access to that place, and any other potential sources of mystical lore (like the Museum of Natural History archives)"
        ],
